label: Hartnett(2010) pubic symphysis morphology stage
definition: A categorical measurement datum describing the morphology of the pubic symphysis of a specific individual according to the method defined by Hartnett (2010).
definition source: Hartnett, K. M. (2010). Analysis of Age-at-Death Estimation Using Data from a New, Modern Autopsy Sample—Part I: Pubic Bone. Journal of Forensic Sciences 55(5). doi: 10.1111/j.1556-4029.2010.01399.x
is about: (rdfbones:AnatomicalRegionOfInterest and 'regional part of' some (fma:fma16585 and obo:BFO_0000050 some (rdfbones:SampleFromHumanSkeletalRemains)))

label: Hartnett (2010) age range
definition: A range of age-at-death estimates that are deemed possible for a specific individual, constituted by a lower and an upper bound.
definition source: Hartnett, K. M. (2010). Analysis of Age-at-Death Estimation Using Data from a New, Modern Autopsy Sample—Part I: Pubic Bone. Journal of Forensic Sciences 55(5). doi: 10.1111/j.1556-4029.2010.01399.x
